In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims March 2012 as Irish-American Heritage Month. He highlights the enduring partnership between America and Ireland, emphasizing the millions of Irish descendants who have made significant contributions to the United States. The President acknowledges the sacrifices made by Irish immigrants, who left behind their homes and belongings to seek a better life. He praises their resilience, hard work, and faith, which helped build America's infrastructure and defend the nation. Obama encourages all Americans to celebrate the contributions of Irish Americans during this month.